System Dynamics Model

An implemention of the model from Duggan’s paper: System Dynamics Modeling with R (Lecture Notes in Social Networks), Duggan, Jim.

A system dynamics representation of the health sector using Shiny. Systems thinking is a departure from linear thinking, as system dynamics attempts to understand nonlinear behaviour of participants over time using stocks, flows, feedback loops, table functions and other functions such as time delays.

To clone this repository, in the terminal:

git clone https://github.com/MaguireMaName/SDM.git

cd SDM
